# FactLockCam Remediation and Hardening Standards

## Configuration & Secret Segregation
- **NEVER** commit secret material, RPC keys, or infrastructure tracking metrics directly into codebase parameters. All configuration targets must be managed via standard compilation injections (`--dart-define`, `dart_defines.json`, repo-root `.env.local` via `scripts/sync_flutter_dart_defines.sh`).
- `factlockcam_app/lib/core/config/generated_dart_defines.dart` and `factlockcam_app/dart_defines.json` MUST remain gitignored.

## Error Handling Constraints
- `MissingPluginException` must **NEVER** be categorized as an environment recovery path. Treat platform channel absences as absolute terminal failures in [`vault_service_io.dart`](factlockcam_app/lib/domain/services/vault_service_io.dart) `_isRecoverableRemoteFailure`.
- Do not treat broad `PlatformException` as recoverable unless the error code is a known transient network/channel case.

## Service Isolation & Dependency Injection
- Do **NOT** invoke raw service locators (`getIt<T>()`) directly within UI widget leaves or ephemeral controller scopes. All dependencies must pass through verified architectural provider interfaces or state notifier contracts.
- Inject `KeyCustodyService` and `IsolateLockCoordinator` into `VaultService` — no `getIt` inside domain service methods.

## Async Naming Rules
- Methods performing network transitions, storage writes, or isolate interactions using the `async` boundary must **NEVER** include the suffix `Sync` in **new** APIs. Existing `retryPendingRemoteSync` / `setPendingSync` names are grandfathered.

## Native Signing
- Release/profile builds must use hardware-backed `signHash` (iOS Secure Enclave, Android Keystore). No `SIMULATED_DEV` payloads in production native targets.
- Courier link generation requires `AppConfig.enableProofLinks` (`ENABLE_PROOF_LINKS` dart-define).
